{"key":"post-15310990","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15310990</id>\n<content>&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;guba said:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Cakes require more work than bulk so the more you scale it the less effective it becomes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/shocked.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:shocked:&quot; title=&quot;:shocked:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cakes:&lt;br /&gt;Mix rice flour, water and vermiculite, load jars:&amp;nbsp; 5 minutes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Steam sterilize in a large pot. 90 minutes.&amp;nbsp; Cool and inject.&amp;nbsp; Wait three to four weeks and fruit.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bulk:&lt;br /&gt;Rinse grains and soak overnight.&amp;nbsp; Bring to a boil, drain and dry, then load bags:&amp;nbsp; 1 to 2 hours, plus overnight.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Inoculate grains and wait for full colonization: Two to three weeks.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Find and shred the bulk substrate material, then bring to field capacity and pasteurize: Several hours.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Take colonized spawn and mix with bulk substrate, and let colonize.&amp;nbsp; Two to three weeks.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/shrug.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:shrug:&quot; title=&quot;:shrug:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Now, neither bulk nor cakes are 'hard', but to say cakes are a waste of time and bulk gives more product is simply incorrect.&amp;nbsp; Size for size, cakes outperform even the best bulk substrates.&amp;nbsp; Ten pounds of brf cakes will give more product than ten pounds of any bulk substrate material known.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;guba said:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt; they are more difficult and require more maintenance. I'm not saying cakes are difficult and bulk is easy. IMO they are almost the same in terms of difficulty, but still I find cakes more difficult. Regards.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/facepalm.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:facepalm:&quot; title=&quot;:facepalm:&quot;/&gt;&amp;nbsp; I'm glad I wasn't your English teacher.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15311043</next>\n<prev>15310880</prev>\n<first>14904750</first>\n<last>15311060</last>\n<when>1320204431</when>\n<utime>11/02/11 06:27 AM</utime>\n</post>"}